Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.95,0:01:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A non-integrist person wouldn't be worried about it.\NIt's because of integrity that you worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.16,0:01:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of spiritual responsibility, you worry about it.\NA person of low integrity wouldn't even be concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.48,0:01:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,about the question.\NBut, like yourself, I tended to be scrupulous.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.74,0:01:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I tended to scrupulosity and perfectionism, you know?\NAgonized everything, whether it was, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.21,0:01:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in today's language, you're above or below 200, you know?\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.52,0:01:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is also about karma.\NMy understanding is that you have said that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.16,0:01:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,animals and people calibrating below 200\Ndo not have individual karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.62,0:01:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't say individual karma.\NThey don't have an awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.22,0:02:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They experience.\NBut they don't realize that that experience
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.19,0:02:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of existence.\NSo they cannot extrapolate that to other human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.97,0:02:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See, over 500, I mean, you know, over 200,\Nyou say, yeah, but how is that gonna affect others
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.57,0:02:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,if I do that?\NBelow 200, you don't care how that affects others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.39,0:02:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's their problem.\NBut over 200, no, you take on spiritual responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.66,0:02:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know what you got that from,\Nwhen I said that you don't develop an etheric body,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.88,0:02:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,etheric brain, until over 200.\NYeah, it's true, you don't have an etheric.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.93,0:02:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, the karma of people below 200 is group karma.\NIt's group karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, from 200 up, you got individual responsibility.\NUp to that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.03,0:03:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're like one of the mob.\NSo by agreement, let's say a mob in front of the guillotine,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.96,0:03:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they're all getting there with their netting,\Nget there early.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.40,0:03:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They love to watch the heads get chopped off, see?\NThey have formed a group karmic energy field, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.56,0:03:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're subject to the karma of that animal level.\NThe cat is subject to the consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.17,0:03:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of the karmic energy field of cat-ness, see?\NWith the exception of the cat's purr
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.95,0:03:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dog's wagging tail.\NAnd you know when we've asked about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.56,0:03:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we said we weren't allowed to ask about it.\NSomething unique about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.24,0:03:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But so, up to 200, you inherit the group karma,\Nthe karma of that group, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.42,0:03:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And then from 200 on, it gets individual,\Nlet's ask that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.62,0:04:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a fact, the Lord resist.\NIt was surprising when we came across it to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.49,0:04:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pick it up faster.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.07,0:04:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the consequences.\Nconsequences of group karma in massive planetary things. How come just they
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.52,0:04:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,were underneath the volcano as it erupted? Everybody knows this thing\Nerupts periodically, and yet they're living there. Why is that? Then they all
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.46,0:04:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,get killed by the volcano. I mean, so obviously a group karmic participation,\Nis it not? Yeah. See, there's also the upside to the group karma, see? Not just
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.04,0:04:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside, but because they experience love of each other in that\Nvillage and attachment to home and the valuation of love and it's various
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.94,0:05:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions. So, there's not just downside, you know, but also upside. Must be something to\Nlove your village so much that you just hang out there even though it's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.14,0:05:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,get buried under a volcano, you know? Just can't leave home, I don't know. I understand them.\NI've got a question about choice, and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.29,0:05:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,very curious about the relationship between the two. You know, it's a lot of\NAbout choice, I'm not really sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.33,0:05:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After listening to some of the things you said,\Nyou said that lots of times you'll have thoughts will come up
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.11,0:05:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and your ego will take credit for them.\NSo how do I know when I'm choosing and when my egos,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.27,0:05:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you said that lots of times thoughts come out of nothingness as well,\Nbut we have free will and choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.35,0:05:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do I tell the difference between the two?\NWell, what's coming up are options.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:06:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming out of a nothingness into a manifestation as thinking this.\NAnd they tend to create options continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.32,0:06:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, should I have a sip of coffee now or not?\NOr should I stop and do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.10,0:06:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I let the coffee wait to that?\NWill he feel offended if I stop and have coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.48,0:06:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NSo like multiple options are existing simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.13,0:06:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The propensity is going to depend on your level of consciousness.\NWhich of the choices are going to seem to be the most attractive, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.94,0:06:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And certain options are going to be zeroed out,\Nnot even an option because of who you've become, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.06,0:06:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's a variety of options and I can choose a multiple number of those options at any time?\NOr does the field determine what I'm going to choose?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.74,0:06:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The field is where it's presented, you might say.\NAnd then you perceive within that field what looked to you to be the,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.36,0:06:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the various options.\NNow you don't have a choice about whether you're going to make a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.56,0:07:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have a choice about making a choice.\NYou've got to make a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.69,0:07:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NWhen your foot's in the air, you've got to put it down somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.78,0:07:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't stand for 20 years with this foot trying to decide.\NSo, the mind works so quickly, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the propensity, so what you're seeing is the consciousness level\Nbrings up propensities and options that would not come at a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.58,0:07:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so then I would be, then I do influence things.\NSo, it's not the same as cause, but it's influenced because it's a part of the...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.19,0:07:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, who you are is the field now.\NIt's influencing the options that have seemed to you, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.19,0:07:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you could say, I could let him die or not let him die.\NNow, at a certain level, you can't let him die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.35,0:07:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,At another level, you've got to let him die.\NSo, what's correct depends on the contextualization of that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.93,0:07:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness, right?\NAt a certain level, it's wrong to let him die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.99,0:08:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Another level, it's wrong to let him live.\NSee what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It all depends on context.\NI understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.99,0:08:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've quoted to this group the guilt I had for a great deal of time\Nthat after goring a guy right in the groin with a spear,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not administer the coup de grace.\NThat was a mistake to let him live.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.95,0:08:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There, I should have.\NOne warrior's obligation to the other brought his suffering to an end,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.40,0:08:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,like you leave one bullet in a revolver, see?\NSo, then it would depend on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.98,0:08:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I had to go through it in this lifetime,\Nand I recall the exact failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.64,0:08:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a moral failure.\NMy obligation is one warrior to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.64,0:08:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You give him an easy way out of this pain and suffering.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it depends on where you're at at the time.\NThat's what I was learning then, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.66,0:09:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is that the influence of that situation,\Nthat's not the same as causing it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.66,0:09:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not causal, no.\NBut what's unresolved gets brought back to choose again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A Course in Miracles presents that nicely.\NI think it's even called choose again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.94,0:09:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're represented, now choose again, see?\NIf that happened with that warrior again,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.94,0:09:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I would, of course, administer the coup de grace.\NI'd say to him, okay, and he'd say okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.53,0:09:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, see how it differs then depending on the context.\NThank you for asking me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.47,0:09:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's ten to four.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.52,0:10:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make the answer shorter.\NI thought we started earlier so I could go on and on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.84,0:10:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can't go on and on.\NI have to be brief and short to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.96,0:10:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been bad again.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NFirst, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.96,0:10:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I flew here with my friend from London yesterday\Nto come and be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.96,0:10:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And 20 years ago when I started on my kind of conscious path\Nof development through being sentenced through the course
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.66,0:10:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to Alcoholics Anonymous and then that kind of started\Nthis whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.66,0:10:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And about every five years in my personal obsession\Nwith my enlightenment, my whole life seems to fall apart
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.82,0:10:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I'm not who I think I am.\NAnd about a year and a half ago I started reading your material
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.82,0:10:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and listening to your tapes and then it really fell apart.\NAnd, you know, my business went, my wife went,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.86,0:11:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the house went, the car went, the children's private schools went,\Nyou know, everything went.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.86,0:11:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I'm living in a tiny little rented flat in London.\NCool.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.86,0:11:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just outside of London.\NAnd I've never had less in terms of, you know, having a lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.86,0:11:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NMy question is when I force myself to make my career work,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.08,0:11:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make it work.\NWhen I surrender myself more and more, I usually end up with less and less.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, like I want to provide for my children\Nand my business is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.08,0:11:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be able to provide for my ex-wife and I've got no work.\NBut I know if I go out there and just, you know, give it some stick
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.08,0:11:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and forget about surrendering everything, I can make things happen.\NBut I don't want to work like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.08,0:11:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I do want to be able to continue to surrender myself to God,\Nto the God of my understanding and be able to provide for my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.08,0:12:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm...\NWhat you're saying is that they're alternate whereas actually they do work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.08,0:12:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can continuously be a provider and also constantly surrender.\NIt's just that you're going to be presented with different things to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,than you would have been if you had not participated back in the workaday world.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.36,0:12:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you live your life in a contemplative style,\Nyou don't have to leave the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.32,0:12:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can still participate in the world, at least up to a certain level.\NSo I would try that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.32,0:12:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Try participating in the world to fulfill that other obligation\Nand continue the spiritual work as a continuous contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.11,0:12:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NCan I ask you one more thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.46,0:12:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I can drive a cab and also be contemplative.\NI've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.46,0:12:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NCan I ask you one more thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.30,0:12:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThe more I try and solve my money problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.30,0:12:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the worse it tends to get.\NAnd...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.78,0:13:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I mean?\NEverything I do is to be able to make more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.78,0:13:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrender to make more money.\NI go out and knock on doors to get business to make more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.78,0:13:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm in this kind of paradox of wanting to give all that up,\Nbut I want to give it all up so I'll have more of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.78,0:13:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can provide.\NAnd I just don't know if I'm missing the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.16,0:13:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you must be.\NGet a job, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind working.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just get a job.\NForget the business.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.82,0:13:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry?\NJust get a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.82,0:13:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget the business, business.\NForget the what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.82,0:13:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Business.\NOh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.82,0:13:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just get a job.\NDeal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.08,0:13:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.17,0:13:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NSimple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.41,0:14:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the Buddha said in my ear, you know.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.91,0:14:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NHi, Dr. David.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.91,0:14:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My question has to do, I know you came in this incarnation with a very honed intellect.\NAnd my question is, you seem to be sharing with us some divine wisdom and knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.14,0:14:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just curious how that comes to you.\NThat's my question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.86,0:14:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't come.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.86,0:14:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.52,0:14:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me explain.\NWhat was becomes replaced by a different state.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.06,0:14:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This state is complete and total within itself.\NThis state is unmoving, non-responsive, has no volition, couldn't care less whether you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.82,0:14:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,learn anything, whether I'm a teacher or not, you know?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.92,0:15:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThen, that presence within responds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.82,0:15:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It uses the intellect as a tool, you know?\NBut actually, there's nobody there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy activates.\NIt activates the apparatus appropriately, depending on who's approaching about what,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.83,0:15:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,see?\NAnd that precipitates back an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.60,0:15:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no knowingness what's going to be said until I've just heard it.\NThere's no, like, think of an answer and then say the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.62,0:15:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that's coming from causality.\NIt just is of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.38,0:15:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's hard to explain.\NBecause the mind thinks in cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.38,0:15:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinks there must be a causal agent, see?\NThat does this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.38,0:15:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't a this that does that.\NIt is, it radiates out of that which it is, spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.01,0:16:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, basically...\NIt's called the Purusha in Sanskrit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.55,0:16:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're dying to know the term, you know?\NSo, your job was to...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.29,0:16:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To...\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.93,0:16:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Cute.\NYou came in as a teacher and then you reached that level where you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.99,0:16:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're open to the teachings being channeled through you?\NI don't get any channeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.99,0:16:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay.\NChanneling is dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.99,0:16:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a that channeling a this to a this, you know?\NIt's a consequence of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.99,0:16:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the radiance of beauty?\NThe flower is not doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.50,0:16:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The flower is that.\NGot it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.50,0:16:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NDidn't come into this world to be beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.50,0:16:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou're projecting an intentuality which is a dualistic conceptualization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.50,0:16:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt radiates what it smells like because of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.86,0:17:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThat's easy, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.86,0:17:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, you are expressing your teacher-ness.\NThat's what the world would call it, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.14,0:17:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd so, each of us has something we came to express.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.30,0:17:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is also a teacher to those who are behind you because we're all on an evolutionary\Nscale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.30,0:17:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo, compared to this one, you're a student, but compared to this one, you're a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.30,0:17:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou know, probably the preponderance of humankind calibrates lower than you do, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.55,0:17:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to them, you radiated an energy which uplifts and sustains them.\NSo, each one is a student of that which is ahead and a teacher to that which is behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.13,0:17:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we are all either a teacher or a student depending on the relationship.\NIf I'm with somebody and he's a better carpenter than I am, then I'm the student and he's the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.22,0:17:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher, see?\NSo, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.22,0:18:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.10,0:18:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.\NI got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to know if it's in my highest good to leave my marriage.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.78,0:18:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a complicated one.\NAnd you'd have to pray for guidance and handle it the best you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.85,0:18:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do that for you because I'd be robbing you of the karmic consequence.\NWell, that's a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.85,0:18:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What I get is that it's a decision.\NAnd it's an important decision because what you're going to do is going to depend on your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.17,0:19:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,values and how you prioritize those values, you know?\NYou see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.51,0:19:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be robbing you of the karmic benefit.\NI'd be making a judgment call.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.76,0:19:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NThat's a tough one for everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.59,0:19:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you for being you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.43,0:19:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My desire is to surrender to God everything but peace and love, which I've learned from\Nyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.23,0:19:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would like to know how best I am to do that.\NIt's by your overall alignment and commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.45,0:19:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, you do it by prayer and by service and asking God's will in all things.\NEvery day in the 12-step groups, you take a moral inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.53,0:20:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And you ask for God's guidance and his will for you.\NHow can I best be of service to thee, O Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.98,0:20:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then that invocation, you put out with great devotional intensity.\NAnd then your life becomes somewhat...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.61,0:20:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What you've just done by virtue of the Heisenberg principle is you've just changed the options\Nthat are going to be coming up for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this was going to be coming up for you.\NWith that invocation, this comes up for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.41,0:20:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NBecause you've just changed the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.41,0:20:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the spiritual intention is already working in people's lives, and they don't recognize\Nit, so they think that they're failing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.50,0:20:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not failing.\NWhat's in front of you right now is the consequence of what you've been asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.10,0:20:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not being able to see, not having any money, all those things are the consequence.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.46,0:20:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.46,0:21:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.\NYou're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.67,0:21:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.40,0:21:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NSo, for years I led a prayer group, and then I hit a point where I was not sure if I should
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.04,0:21:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for some reason.\NShould pray?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.04,0:21:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not...\NWell, as a group.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.04,0:21:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To lead a group.\NTo lead a group in a healing ministry kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.04,0:21:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh.\NLead a prayer group.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.04,0:21:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.23,0:21:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guess that sort of is my question.\NIs there a value in praying together as a group for people that request it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.23,0:21:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so.\NBecause, as I said here, the intention of the student, the intention of the teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.23,0:21:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and the intention of the group, the three together form a very powerful field.\NSo when people group together in prayer, a prayer group is a very positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.23,0:22:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, silent unity, for instance.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.23,0:22:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles happen all the time out of silent unity.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.90,0:22:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.45,0:22:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea.\NDr. Hawkins, could you talk about some of the differences between a student and a prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.48,0:22:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,group?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.48,0:22:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A state that might be psychologically destabilizing and one that might be spiritually\Ngrowthful?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.48,0:22:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not be able to tell the difference, because sometimes spiritual growth seems to\Nmanifest as a psychological disorder temporarily, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.74,0:22:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all your values and your paradigm of reality may shift, see?\NSo there's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.67,0:23:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I just wrote about it in one chapter, that there's periods in the spiritual evolution,\Nof confusion and disorientation, and am I doing the right thing, and should I be living
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.23,0:23:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,this way?\NThere's periods of doubt and uncertainty, periods of upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.86,0:23:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because evolution, as we said today, is in a way revolution.\NEvolution upsets the routine order of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.51,0:23:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're staying still and not moving spiritually, you won't have any disruption, see?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.46,0:23:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you begin to shift values.\NLet's say when a person first takes their moral inventory, their view of themself may
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.47,0:23:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,change quite a bit, just as a consequence of that, and may have some psychological disruption\Nperiod, temporarily at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.86,0:23:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIs there any place where we should show caution?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.29,0:24:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's too general in a way to ask, yes.\NThere are boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.01,0:24:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There are boundaries.\NIn fact, in the books I'm finishing, I'm making clear the boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.83,0:24:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's certain places I advise people not to go.\NThe supernormal, investigating the paranormal, the supernormal, the lower astral realms,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.31,0:24:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,invisible entities.\NYou don't know how to play in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.20,0:24:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know how to play there.\NI wouldn't play there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.24,0:24:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know how to play there.\NYou're not equipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.24,0:24:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't handle this world.\NWhat the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.24,0:24:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking at another dimension, and you have the slightest understanding of what's\Ngoing on there, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.60,0:24:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're a bee, you're a witless babe to these entities.\NThey've been at it for eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.46,0:24:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NMaybe the channels that exist today were exactly the same in Mesopotamia.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.27,0:24:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo if they were that spiritually evolved, they would have moved up to celestial realms
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.04,0:25:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,quite a few centuries ago.\NSo therefore, I don't approve of seeking anything outside of what you can see, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.06,0:25:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, momentary transitional periods of confusion and upset are pretty normal.\NYou know, when you confront yourself about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.02,0:25:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, something will come up, and you're disturbed for a couple of days about this.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.23,0:25:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're looking at what it means and all the stuff it brings up, you know?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.09,0:25:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.09,0:25:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIt's pretty normal for a cavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.75,0:25:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't figure out how to get upset, you're probably not working on yourself too\Nmuch, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.62,0:25:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't think about suicide at least once a week.\NYou ain't moving on from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.62,0:25:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm excited.\NI'm excited.
