Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.36,0:35:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,a person's subconscious negative beliefs\Nabout himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.88,0:36:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, if used within the correct context,\NI think it's a useful tool, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.40,0:36:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on what your intention is.\NIf you're looking for a magical cure
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.00,0:36:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or something, I don't think that's\Nthe proper use, but you could use
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.54,0:36:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hypnosis to get to the roots of it\Nso that you see what the roots
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.52,0:36:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the problem are.\NMaybe go on a path, you could do a past lifetime, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.56,0:36:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to see maybe its historical origin.\NI would use it for clarification rather than
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.64,0:36:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to sort of magically cure something\Nand accomplish something.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.18,0:36:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I would use it for deeper inner insight.\NAnd I think it's a useful tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.06,0:36:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, with that, then what would you say would be\Nthe best tool for someone to fix self-esteem?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.41,0:36:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,To fix self-esteem?\NWell, self-esteem isn't just a thing, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.89,0:36:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a component.\NYou can't just pause it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.52,0:36:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the overall level of the ocean, you know.\NYou can't just change the level of the ocean, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.52,0:37:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-esteem, first of all, is a judgment, you see.\NBut no, in every case, it's rather complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.63,0:37:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's valuable to you because it drives you\Nwithin to understand yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.27,0:37:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll arrive at the answer yourself.\NYou'll arrive at the answer yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.94,0:37:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be some self-condemnation\Nyou have.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.28,0:37:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You've forgotten.\NIt could be somebody programmed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.44,0:37:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to cancel that program.\NSee, one's esteem should not be a matter of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.00,0:37:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,come see, come saw.\NIt's a gone conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.55,0:37:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a done.\NIt's a done.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.19,0:37:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a matter to be questioned.\NYour value or your worth is not a matter of question.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.79,0:37:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Your existence already answers whether you're worth anything.\NGod created you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.64,0:37:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what more do you want?\NYou came from Wal-Mart, so I mean, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.12,0:38:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.42,0:38:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Life via God, body by Wal-Mart, yeah?\NGeneral Motors.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.86,0:38:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Body by General Motors.\NWhat did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.10,0:38:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Life by God, body by Wal-Mart?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.18,0:38:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, self-worth, you're denying the divinity of your own essence,\Nyour creation, you know, which is created of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.91,0:38:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hardly ask, what is this worth, you know?\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.81,0:38:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My question to you is, what is this worth?\NTo you is surrendering everything to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.64,0:38:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I say, and this too, Lord, I often go, well, maybe I'll do it.\NYou winced, you winced, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.03,0:38:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And all my money too, God.\NWell, I surrendered my youth and good luck, and you see what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.46,0:38:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And with children as well.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.22,0:39:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that they're, like, I know that they're in the hands of the Lord,\Nbut then just to let them go, you know, as they get older.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.41,0:39:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes, I understand that, but just to do it without guilt of being, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.34,0:39:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, just...\NAll right, so it brings up stuff a lot with a kid, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.64,0:39:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's attachment, there's control.\NNot only to relinquish them to live their own life,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.34,0:39:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but to fulfill their own karma, see, you know?\NCorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.42,0:39:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's being a good parent, of course, is sooner or later you've got to let them go.\NAs far as a linear control...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.08,0:39:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Relationship.\NBut not as far as the contextualization of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.98,0:39:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which is beyond distance and presence and physicality.\NSo the love you have for them, they've already incorporated.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.58,0:39:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They better...\NYou see, the love that you give to the child in and of itself is worthless
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.13,0:40:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,unless the child incorporates it in their own self-concept.\NThe child who's been deprived of love in early childhood
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.42,0:40:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,hasn't incorporated it.\NThe good, loving parent can't really experience themself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.33,0:40:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as loving or lovable or worthwhile.\NIt could be they've already picked up that energy from you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.92,0:40:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and they don't need it anymore in a direct fashion, one-to-one fashion,\Nbecause they've already adopted that principle, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.30,0:40:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But for me to let that go, like, I know my children know how to love\Nand that I have been a loving parent,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.10,0:40:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but then as they go...\Nthrough their life, and not to worry...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.49,0:40:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, not to worry?\NWell, you know, something might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.49,0:40:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way you can not worry is to be dead, you know?\NThe infant's worried the minute it's born.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.58,0:41:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It begins crying and bawling and mewling.\NThe mother's worried the minute it's born.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.58,0:41:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The nurses are worried. The doctor's worried.\NThe neighbors are worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.58,0:41:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to not worry? Yeah, God bless you.\NYou don't worry hard enough. That's your problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.38,0:41:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you, Dr. Hawkins.\NAnd I bring all the love and blessings of every member
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.73,0:41:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Dr. Hawkins Study Group in Albuquerque\Nand in Santa Fe.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.73,0:41:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We love you.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.73,0:41:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a religious science practitioner,\Nand since studying with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.73,0:41:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come into a great deal of conflict\Nabout the method of prayer that is used in religious science.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.73,0:42:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a lot of people come to me\Nand ask me to pray for them, you know, for specific things.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.73,0:42:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the whole idea behind a prayer in religious science is\Nthat you have what's called the realization stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.73,0:42:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,where you affirm or claim that this good\Nis coming to this person's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.73,0:42:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That good is coming to this person's life?\NYeah, the particular good that they mention.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.76,0:42:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, their particular good, yeah.\NYeah, and it brings me into a lot of conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.76,0:42:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've heard you say, and, you know,\Nit's the absolute truth, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.76,0:42:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't want to interfere in someone's karma.\NWell, you can't anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.76,0:42:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and so, right, and, you know,\Nyou don't want to try because then, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.76,0:42:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember you answered a question\Nabout a lady whose sister was alcoholic,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.76,0:42:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and you said, you know, you're just,\Nevery time you rescue her, you're pushing her further away.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.76,0:42:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so all of this has come to play\Nin my attempts to pray for people
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.76,0:42:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who come and ask me to pray for some particular good,\Nand I'm thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.76,0:43:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but you're seeing yourself as a doer.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.76,0:43:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not a doer, my dear.\NYou're only a presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.76,0:43:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the presence plus your intention\Nis all that you can do as a prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.76,0:43:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as the prayer person.\NAnd the acceptance of that, the fulfillment of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.76,0:43:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on their personal karma.\NYou're not going to override it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.76,0:43:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not like you're overriding a person's personal karma.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.76,0:43:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you pray, dear Lord, for a healing\Nto the degree that it can be done
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.76,0:43:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by that divine grace and mercy, you see,\Nand now it's up to divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.04,0:43:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's a little bit different from\Nwhat we are told, from how we're told to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.49,0:43:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, say it again, how you do it.\NWe just affirm that this particular good
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.49,0:43:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming to this person's life,\Nlike if they want a really good job or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.49,0:43:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, it's okay, it's optimism.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.49,0:43:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So we affirm that this person here present,\Nabout whom we are praying,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.52,0:44:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,will be coming into the needed job\Nto support his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.52,0:44:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Right? Is that it?\NSomething, yeah, something like that, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.52,0:44:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NYou're not going to violate their karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.52,0:44:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because if...\Nit's not going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.52,0:44:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The very fact that they've asked you to pray for them\Nhas already changed their karma, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.52,0:44:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.65,0:44:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe very fact that they've asked God's help,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.65,0:44:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're just an avenue with that.\NI'm a vehicle, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.65,0:44:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay.\NSo you're just an avenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.65,0:44:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still up to divinity\Nand propensity of proclivity
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.74,0:44:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of manifesting an actuality out of a potentiality,\Nwhich you're just one of the agents in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.66,0:44:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd we do think of ourselves as vehicles,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.66,0:44:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet I want to pray accordingly,\Nyou know, according to God's grace and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.66,0:44:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's just,\Nit's not something that you say in a religious science prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.66,0:44:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NOr is it verboten?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.66,0:45:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, do they excommunicate you or something?\NIs it in accordance with God's will?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.66,0:45:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I never got that out of religious science,\Nthat it's that restrictive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.66,0:45:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think it would be verboten.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.66,0:45:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'm having trouble finding the correct wording.\NYeah, I think that's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.66,0:45:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou're uncertain how to contextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.66,0:45:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYou can just add,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.66,0:45:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in accordance with thy will, O Lord.\NAnd in accordance with the highest good, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.24,0:45:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I see.\NI see a Mercury coming into your future,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.24,0:45:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a Ford,\Nall in accordance with God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.24,0:45:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A new SUV.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.24,0:45:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, sweetheart.\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.24,0:45:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it is just the way you were contextualizing it\Nyou were worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.24,0:45:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NYeah, we did a sermon at a workshop at religious science
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.43,0:45:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,about a month ago.\NBrother, we've always asked for a Mercedes Benz.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.78,0:45:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NWe've always asked for a Mercedes Benz.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.78,0:45:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NAnd a Mercedes Benz, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.19,0:46:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Mercedes Benz.\NDoctor, it's my understanding that it's more spiritually advantageous
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.19,0:46:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the ego as a friend rather than an adversary.\NSo I've become quite concerned lately
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.19,0:46:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,about the behavior of my friend, the ego.\NThe friend who?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.19,0:46:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,His friend, ego.\NHe's become concerned about the behavior of his friend, ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.19,0:46:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.\NSo when you were in the depths of the pits of hell with the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.19,0:46:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally he let go,\Nwas the ego capable of learning anything from that experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.48,0:46:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It disappeared.\NDisappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.48,0:46:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Got frightened.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.48,0:46:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Frightened.\NFrightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.48,0:46:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Frightened.\NFrightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.48,0:46:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Frightened.\NFrightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.67,0:46:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Frightened.\NFrightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.91,0:46:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Frightened.\NFrightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.91,0:46:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Frightened.\NFrightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.91,0:47:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No, flames are the upper part of hell, that's just the frosting on the cake.\NHi, Dr. Hawking?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.03,0:47:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOkay, you got to get it over here and into the mic.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.29,0:47:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.\NHow does one cultivate love so it's not objectified?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.29,0:47:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's a capacity, a way of being, in the appreciation\Nthat all of creation is the unfolding of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.26,0:47:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution is the unfolding of divinity, of the unmanifest becoming manifest and discernible via linearity.\NSo your consciousness is like a probe from the non-linear into the linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.62,0:47:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThe incredible beauty of the flowers, you see, is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.16,0:48:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He's saying you're done.\NI'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.04,0:48:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this microphone correct?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.71,0:48:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSee, as you evolve, the incredible beauty of everything begins to shine forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.86,0:48:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, you only see it in that which is blatantly aesthetically pleasing.\NAs it goes on, you begin to see it in everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.21,0:48:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that everything is perfect and everything is incredibly beautiful.\NIf we had enough time, I'd tell you about it, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.75,0:48:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to ask you if you would ohm.\NShe wants you to do an ohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.37,0:48:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico did an ohm.\NShe wants you to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.27,0:49:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you want me to do an ohm?\NBecause you do a good ohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.13,0:49:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You ohmed in my son's face, and he said his knees buckled, and so I thought, well, I want that too.\NI did an ohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.79,0:49:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was another time.\NYeah, when he met you previously.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.37,0:49:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.33,0:49:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You better get crazy soon.\NYou keep telling me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.87,0:49:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to just.\NNo, you're going to flip out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.35,0:50:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect to get ohm today, by golly.\NThat was a different lifetime where I did ohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.18,0:50:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, we all did ohm together.\NCaught amongst through eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.87,0:50:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.48,0:50:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is about karma.\NCan you give us some more understanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.54,0:50:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Of how to release accumulated negative karma?\NHow do you want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.66,0:50:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How to release an accumulated negative karma?\NOh, the undoing of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.68,0:50:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The undoing of it.\NWell, that's the purpose of this lifetime, undo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.04,0:50:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're presented with the same thing you didn't forgive before, and now this time you've got the option to forgive it.\NSo it's like a representation of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.28,0:51:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So by striving, you gain good karma, you might say.\NAnd you are presented with limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.00,0:51:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the constant letting go of the limitation, negative feelings and perceptions.\NIt's a continuous process.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.28,0:51:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I can describe it as a contemplative way of being in the world.\NYour life becomes the prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.56,0:51:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the supplication to divinity by the quality of your presentation to God.\NYou are the mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.87,0:51:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the mood.\NYou are the mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.29,0:51:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is you be this.\NNow you don't have to do anything, verbalize anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.00,0:51:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the prayer by virtue of the alignment and contextualization of your existence.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.91,0:52:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life becomes a supplication and an invocation.\NYour life becomes the prayer of invocation by which your existence is constantly reflecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.50,0:52:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The divinity and will of God as it's comprehensible to this level of consciousness now.\NYou don't have to worry about it because you are it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.78,0:52:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you describe the relationship between mind and consciousness?\NWell, mind generally means mentation, mentalization, intellectualization, visualization, ideas, memories, you know, consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.29,0:52:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ask me about that?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.99,0:53:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is the underlying field which itself is non-linear.\NIt's the light by which you see the linearity of the thinkingness, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.66,0:53:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know that you're thinking?\NHow do you know you're thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.93,0:53:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,By being aware.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.15,0:53:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,By becoming aware.\NHow come you're aware?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.61,0:53:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does awareness come from?\NIs that consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.57,0:53:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You woke up with it.\NYou came into this life with consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.15,0:53:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThe consciousness is not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.09,0:53:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a quality you have.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.47,0:53:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's protoplasmic.\NYou didn't create protoplasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.56,0:53:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are, you know, you came into this life with protoplasm.\NThe capacity to be aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.03,0:53:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say, you know, as a contemplative lifestyle or a meditative style, you would draw from\Nidentification with the movie and the linearity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.61,0:53:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You move into the awareness of self as the witness observer.\NThe witness observer witnesses all the time, watches.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.79,0:53:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't get involved or participate.\NIt doesn't judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.87,0:54:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't think about that.\NIt witnesses it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.13,0:54:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NIt's like a spectator.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.01,0:54:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you move out of participating in the movie to the witness of the movie, then you're\Nthe watcher of the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.55,0:54:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you say, the watcher of the witness, where do they come from?\NThey come from awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.62,0:54:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness comes from consciousness.\NConsciousness comes from divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.02,0:54:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nonlinear.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.16,0:54:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAs you move your identification out of the out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.42,0:54:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Out there-ness, you'll see that what is innate is an impersonal quality that's independent\Nof you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.69,0:54:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's getting closer and closer to the self as consciousness.\NSo how could consciousness by error choose oneness or singleness?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.97,0:54:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how can consciousness error?\NBecause you said it in chapter 18 of this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.59,0:54:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How can consciousness error?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.73,0:55:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You said.\NConsciousness can.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.31,0:55:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,By error, no.\NYou said by error can.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.95,0:55:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I got the word right?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.67,0:55:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe I'm saying it wrong.\NThe error occurs within consciousness itself before there is even any person involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.74,0:55:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness can experience itself either as singularity or as oneness.\NHow?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.88,0:55:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That is mine to me.\NI mean, I'm confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.24,0:55:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't quite understand your question.\NIt's the chapter 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.99,0:55:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHow?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.55,0:55:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How do spiritual errors come about?\NThat's a pretty general question.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.62,0:55:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have taken an hour to answer that.\NHow do spiritual errors come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.96,0:55:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really asking the nature of consciousness itself.\NIs the a priori quality out of which awareness arises?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.95,0:55:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's the background feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.25,0:56:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the background field out of which awareness then becomes progressive.\NIt expresses to the witness, the observer, and then the witnesser, the observer of the linear what, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.63,0:56:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But independent of what, what, is the innate nonlinear quality of consciousness itself, which prevails all the time, you know?\NYou all see?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.06,0:56:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, look past the content.\NUnderneath the mind is an infinite field of stillness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.19,0:56:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can focus on that any time.\NYou don't have to go into a meditative state.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.37,0:56:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Be aware that it's like the ocean, and the thoughts are like the fish flying out.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.88,0:56:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on that which, what is the condition just before the thinkingness arises?\NNot linear sequentially, but the substrate of all thinkingness, out of which all thinkingness arises, is an infinite field always available.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.15,0:57:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you are, the infinite field of consciousness, which is, which is vacant of content.\NIt's like space.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.03,0:57:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Space exists independent of whether there's anything.\NAnything in it or not is going to drive me crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.71,0:57:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's 22.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.05,0:57:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.17,0:57:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move along faster.\NWe got a good one coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.91,0:57:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.18,0:57:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, all.\NI'd like to thank you all for being supportive, and in this group, I have gained a lot of strength and courage facing my situation right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.96,0:57:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is, I'd like to seek advice on how to deal with my heart.\NMy heart hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.14,0:57:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart has been beating very nervously, very fast, in the past year and a half.\NAnd it gets intensified when I'm exposed to spiritual teachings, spiritual teachers, and spiritual groups like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.13,0:58:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Like when I read the book, I, in the evening.\NIs it better or worse?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.17,0:58:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets worse.\NWorse?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.81,0:58:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Very exciting.\NOh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.63,0:58:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like overwhelming.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.43,0:58:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yeah, I like to, like, I try different things.\NLike I try to argue.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.52,0:58:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, puncture.\NDidn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.64,0:58:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NI went to a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.64,0:58:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, my heart is no problem.\NParoxysmal tachycardia?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.58,0:58:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he call it?\NParoxysmal tachycardia?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.75,0:58:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he suggest a beta blocker?\NA beta blocker.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.58,0:58:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that cuts down overreaction to adrenaline?\NI never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.67,0:58:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't suggest a beta blocker.\NOrdinarily, a beta blocker would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.66,0:58:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everything that's physical, mental, and spiritual.\NSo, you want to block off the symptom itself, but at the same time, you also want to see the origin of it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.02,0:58:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIt's just emotional excitement as you get closer and closer to spiritual truth, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.52,0:58:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NSo, what would.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.44,0:58:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Tachycardia.\NHe needs a beta blocker, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.44,0:58:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.44,0:59:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I would try a simple beta blocker.\NThey're very cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.44,0:59:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Generic.\NBeta blocker.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.44,0:59:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Beta blocker.\NThey call.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.44,0:59:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you write it down here?\NWhat's in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.54,0:59:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Midoprolol.\NMidoprolol.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.54,0:59:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to prescribe as a physician now, but you should ask your doctor.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.64,0:59:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you.\NBut when I go to him, then he listen to my heart, and then he beats normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.64,0:59:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.64,0:59:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When I visit the doctor.\NWhen he sees the doctor, it's beating normally.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.64,0:59:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NWell, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.64,0:59:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See, he doesn't have to see the tachycardia.\NYou just tell him, you know, I have periodic periods of tachycardia, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.64,0:59:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need a tranquilizer for that.\NYou don't need the tranquilizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.64,0:59:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A beta blocker decreases sensitivity to adrenaline.\NYou may react to excitement over adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.64,0:59:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.64,0:59:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NSo, is it going to be a transition thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.08,0:59:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can just take it for a while, and then I.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.08,0:59:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.08,0:59:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just symptomatic.\NYou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.08,0:59:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.08,0:59:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.08,0:59:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.08,0:59:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.08,0:59:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'm going to take it for a while.\NYou can take it very low dose.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.08,0:59:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NIt sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.08,0:59:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that's.\NSee, everything's physical, mental, and spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.08,0:59:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NSo, that's the physical, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.08,1:00:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the mental, I don't know, the excitement.\NAnd the emotional, I'm not sure about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.72,1:00:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, that would take some period of investigation.\NWe couldn't have probably reached it just in a question and answer period.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.82,1:00:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NA related question is, when I go to, like, crowded places, like to subway in big cities.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.14,1:00:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThen I feel I share the emotions of the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.14,1:00:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd they kind of worsen my organs.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.08,1:00:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NLike, my heart sometimes feel beating very fast, my stomach tight, or I feel agony, loneliness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.08,1:00:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,emptiness.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.08,1:00:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNo, that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.08,1:00:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you need to just continue working on a spiritual level, and you'll transcend all\Nthat.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.37,1:00:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, beta blockers are very cheap.\NYou know, I shouldn't ask you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.37,1:00:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the temporary.\NThe physical, the mental, and the spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.37,1:00:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.37,1:00:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the Course in Miracles says the physical, the mental, and the spiritual.\NBecause the physical is only the expression of the intention of the spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.37,1:00:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NPeople think, you know, if I pray for a job, it's going to come out of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.37,1:01:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember a guy said, I prayed and prayed for a job, and nothing happened.\NAnd if it hadn't been for my brother-in-law calling me up, I'd still be unemployed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.29,1:01:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NGod didn't answer his prayer for a job, and his brother-in-law saved him.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.28,1:01:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't see the consequences.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.28,1:01:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.28,1:01:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.34,1:01:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Beta blockers are cheap.\NThey're pretty safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.34,1:01:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I'm talking about temporary relief, you know.\NLong-term, you'll transcend this whole level of anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.34,1:01:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is a medical question.\NIf the calibration level of a physician can influence the outcome of a treatment, does
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.56,1:01:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibration level of the patient also influence?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.56,1:01:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.\NYou've got an interaction of two energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.56,1:01:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.\NBut that's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.56,1:01:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, being a physician, a lot of times I can't control the calibration level of\Nthe patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.56,1:01:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct.\NBut the calibration level is reflecting their karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.56,1:02:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So they may be karmically entitled to a recovery, or they may not.\NAnd your field may or not, you know, you can't impose your will on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.88,1:02:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So you do your intention, you do your physical.\NI suggest you're on the physical, mental, and spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.01,1:02:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tell them, physically this is what I do, mentally this is what I do, and spiritually\Nthis is what I advise.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.59,1:02:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's up to them, see?\NI think all things are physical, mental, and spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.87,1:02:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NTake a beta blocker and also go to the Course of Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.22,1:02:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Also go to the Course of Miracles and see a good psychotherapist.\NNow you're doing it at an all-terrain level.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.22,1:02:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this authentic here?\NIsn't that funny?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.22,1:02:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know anything else?\NOh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.22,1:02:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want me to sign this?\NYeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.22,1:02:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that authentic, that dedication?\NIsn't that cute?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.22,1:02:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's really adorable.\NOh, it probably is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.22,1:02:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the longest part.\NYeah, that's the reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.41,1:02:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Dr. Hawkins.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.41,1:02:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.41,1:02:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.41,1:02:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.41,1:02:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.51,1:02:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.51,1:02:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.51,1:02:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.51,1:03:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As you probably remember, I'm a medical doctor.\NAnd, I've surrendered to God and try to make my life an instrument of divine will.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.94,1:03:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And within this year, I've left two positions.\NYou know, one I kind of used the fact that it was interrupting my coming here as an excuse,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.57,1:03:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other one, more recently, seemed to be a test.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.44,1:03:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was wondering if you could affirm this or not I went to this position that\Nthere was such a macabre bunch of people of the lower realms it seemed like they
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.30,1:03:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,were they were symbolic of vampires and it became so so obvious to me that I was\Nand that I was going to be you know tarnished by by fraud or bad stuff you know I mean I even
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.62,1:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,described it from my mother and she said what are you still doing there you know there's nothing I\Ncan actually prove but it would you know but I left that and I was wondering you know because
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.96,1:04:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read and you probably said too that the as you advance along the path these things come at\Nyou more and more you know as tests there you just decline the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.30,1:04:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah yeah could you do you see if that was a test yeah it's just you decline the option\Nyeah doesn't mean you can't briefly you know participate well I did before I found out
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.02,1:04:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because I didn't want to yeah but then as the as the essence begins to reveal itself you withdraw\Nyeah yeah you were true that was good that's good I get the sense that's great do you know
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.93,1:04:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,dr. Miriam Yost is this because I mean I just got this from\NI don't know from Amazon and it's hard it's hard to remember so many years over the years thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.53,1:05:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,very much I once had a member of the Mafia when I was in trouble treating back I remember the\NMafia and his mother had a severe depression severe bad no response to antidepressants and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.65,1:05:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I said well probably a color shock she should come out of it and so we laid the money says\NI'll put you in events that's rolling out the bills
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.64,1:05:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,she better do alright you know what I mean\Nshe better do it right you know what I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.30,1:05:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,well thankfully thankfully after about three treatments she snapped right out of it\Num having heard the uh Lotus Sutra recited before we
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.77,1:05:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,left or you gotta talk closer to the microphone what was the question\Num
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.59,1:06:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Having heard the Lotus Sutra recited today before we left for lunch, I just wanted to\Nask what the connection between Nam-myoho-renge-kyo and your teachings is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.09,1:06:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand what she said.\NShe wants to know what Nikko's chant has to do with your teachings.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.16,1:06:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Nikko's chant is just a way of doing the Aum because the Kabir is over 700.\NThe music we play is also over 700.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.64,1:06:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's to create a context in which the busyness of the world tends to recede and you tend\Nto go in a higher field, you more quickly get spiritual information.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.64,1:06:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt's hard to get spiritual information in a casino, you're just in the wrong context.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.66,1:06:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Although one time we did one, you had to walk through the casino to give the lecture, didn't\Nwe?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.66,1:07:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.\NDr. Hawkins, when you look at the scale of consciousness, you immediately see how
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.51,1:07:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,mathematically perfect it is that all the significant points occur in very round numbers.\NThat's because I rounded them off.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.51,1:07:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIs that true?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.51,1:07:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not really 200 or 400 or 500?\NNo, no, it isn't literal.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.51,1:07:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the calibrations are usually round out to the nearest five.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.58,1:07:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to do meticulous research on some very specific subject, then it would\Nmake a difference if you move one or two points.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.28,1:07:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NBut generally, you get a letter from somebody and somebody will ship me something and I'll,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.18,1:07:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,without opening it, say, you know, what this calibrates are.\NIf it's under 200, then I put it over in that pile.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.08,1:07:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You open it.\NBut, for example, 600 is not the exact number.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.08,1:07:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the exact number.\NIt's not the exact number.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.81,1:07:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the exact number.\NIt's not the exact number.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.81,1:07:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the exact number.\NIt's not the exact number.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.31,1:08:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the exact number.\NIt's not the exact number.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.31,1:08:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,600 is not exactly that.\NIt's a rounded number.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.31,1:08:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is a rounded number.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.31,1:08:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, whether you're at 598, 602, you know, I mean, you're in a field.\NAnd the field of bliss begins to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.47,1:08:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So the field that you could say, if you could meticulously calibrate every incident, it's\Nat 595, 599, 600, 601, 602.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.51,1:08:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.31,1:08:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could do micro-research.\NVery seldom do we need micro-research, you know, because you're just trying to, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.63,1:08:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what general energy field is this representing, you know what I'm saying?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.29,1:08:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.80,1:09:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIt's an honor to be here next to you, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.04,1:09:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Doris Ann, and I am a practicing, new practice, holistic...\NPracticing what?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.22,1:09:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?\NPractice?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.22,1:09:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,New.\NA new practice, practitioner of holistic kinesiology in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.22,1:09:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.22,1:09:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NAnd my question to you is that I have found that sometimes, whenever I'm working
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.22,1:09:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with somebody, that they could benefit by me clearing out what is in their DNA blueprint.\NYou're going to clear in them?
