Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.44,1:17:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and if whatever level you're at that's not there that ain't it thank you yeah\Nokay well my question is about remembering I guess so my first time
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.34,1:17:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,here I think I understand that we're supposed to try and grow along the\Nspiritual path and I think it takes effort to do that and I'll put forward
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.46,1:17:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the effort and then I'll look back and three days\Nhave gone by and I've been a weenie for three days.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.52,1:17:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I need to\NI need some practical advice about
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.26,1:17:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,how to recover.\NWell, the constancy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.94,1:17:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The Course in Miracles calls it faithfulness.\NConstancy. The 12-step groups
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.26,1:17:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,say you live it one day at a time.\NDon't worry about whether you didn't do it for three days.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.32,1:17:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only supposed to be worrying about today.\NSo your intention
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.30,1:17:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to follow that\Npractice or spiritual practice, whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.10,1:17:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're doing today, is\Nall you don't have to worry about yesterday or the day
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.42,1:18:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,before. That's not a reality.\NThe only reality is your decision in the now.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.36,1:18:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Faithfulness,\Nintuitiveness, persistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.15,1:18:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt corrects itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.77,1:18:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NMy question has to do with, I understand that the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.13,1:18:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is like our animal nature.\NAnd my question is
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.56,1:18:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,if the ego is like the animal,\Ndid God create the ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.55,1:18:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really ask the question.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.77,1:18:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the way you're\Ndefining the ego and God in your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.86,1:18:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Life evolves\Nspontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.35,1:18:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it continues\Nto evolve because consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.01,1:18:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to return to its source.\NOne of its potentialities,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.18,1:18:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because its potentialities\Nare unlimited,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.42,1:18:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is to evolve as the animal\Nkingdom. Then from the animal kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.38,1:19:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it would obviously begin to evolve\Nbeyond the animal kingdom because it's seeking to
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.36,1:19:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,return to its source.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.43,1:19:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you want to do is avoid any\Njudgmentalism about
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.15,1:19:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,how creation\Nappears to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.77,1:19:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because let's say\Nby calibrating, there's an inference
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.03,1:19:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that one thing is better than another.\NIt's not really better.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.98,1:19:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing can become the perfection\Nof its own level.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.04,1:19:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfect amoeba is the perfect amoeba\Nthat's already fulfilled
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.30,1:19:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection within its own domain.\NOkay. Yeah. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.20,1:19:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is\NBoone Gordon from Silverthorne, Colorado
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.60,1:19:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and a World War II fighter pilot.\NI came back from the war
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.12,1:19:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and I noticed\Nthat there was a sense of community
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.66,1:20:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that we had in our fighter squadron.\NAnd I also noticed there wasn't
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.64,1:20:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,this purpose we had in the war.\NAnd I also noticed that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.22,1:20:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't much spirituality.\NWhen we were fighter pilots, we seemed to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.52,1:20:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,tap into the source.\NAnyway, so about 1950
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.16,1:20:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I started meditating\Nwith Raja Yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.06,1:20:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I started getting these messages\Non how to design a town of the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.00,1:20:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so\Nnow these ideas are mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.00,1:20:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're on this book here for you.\NOh, isn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.36,1:20:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question is\NI think that most of the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.40,1:20:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,ideas are above 500 consciousness.\NI call it LQ.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.30,1:20:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, light quotient.\NAnd now my question is,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.28,1:20:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I get this word out?\NAnd how can I find the people
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.68,1:20:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,for this town of the future?\NAny suggestions?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.76,1:20:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, I don't know.\NYou're going to put out a call.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.24,1:20:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this is putting out a call right here\Nfor people to join you in this quest.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.62,1:20:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the quest is what?\NTo establish sort of a heavenly state
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.40,1:21:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,here on Earth or in other dimensions?\NWell, we want to build an actual city
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.69,1:21:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because then people will look and see\Nthat this higher consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.57,1:21:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, a city of light.\NA city of light.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.13,1:21:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,On the physical realm?\NIt's a physical realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.35,1:21:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you're too old for that.\NI understand that 1,200 of us
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.16,1:21:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are dying each day in World War II.\NBut I think I have a couple years left.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.28,1:21:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I think a city of light\Nwould take, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.71,1:21:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,something more than a few years.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.49,1:21:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I think if you hold it in mind,\Nthen that tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.75,1:21:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can certainly join with artists\Nto hold it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.59,1:21:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But the practicality of how to manifest it\Nin the linear domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.09,1:21:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.37,1:21:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a lot of money?\NDon't have any money.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.89,1:21:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need money.\NYou can have it all figured out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.77,1:21:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay, the vision would...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.59,1:21:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, I think I know what you're saying.\NYes, I already got what you said.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.15,1:22:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got the whole design\Nthat you have in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.43,1:22:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI'm not saying it's not doable.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.97,1:22:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you're questioning\Nis really how to present it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.25,1:22:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and create an attraction to the idea.\NYes, correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.27,1:22:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NHow to promulgate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.91,1:22:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NBecause...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.79,1:22:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than writing a book,\Nabout it,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.39,1:22:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or talking on the radio,\Nor I don't know how else.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.02,1:22:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah, that's adorable.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.49,1:22:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NYes, my name is Vishali Shaheen.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.73,1:22:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm from Oakland, California.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.51,1:22:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is,\Nabout two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.57,1:22:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I liquidated all my assets\Nin order to pay off my debt
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.47,1:22:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and save some money\Nand moved in with friends
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.31,1:22:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and living very quietly.\NAnd after a few years of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.93,1:22:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course,\NI'm on a spiritual path,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.49,1:22:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I just kind of went,\Nwow, it would be nice
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.29,1:22:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to have more in my life.\NA relationship, a home,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.91,1:22:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,things like that.\NAs I'm getting older.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.09,1:22:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question is,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.97,1:23:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in wanting a better life,\NI don't want to create more karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.08,1:23:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And...\NWell, you're always going to create karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.92,1:23:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe good karma.\NWhat's wrong with just living a normal life?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.71,1:23:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that would be.\NRight now, we don't see
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.67,1:23:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,how I'm living a normal life.\NRight now, I'm living with friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.47,1:23:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NBut a normal life to me
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.21,1:23:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a home,\Na relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.93,1:23:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so how do you bring that\Ninto manifestation?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.93,1:23:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what you're asking?\NNo, I'm going to,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.31,1:23:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to bring that\Ninto manifestation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.07,1:23:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess my intention\Nis to make sure that I
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.35,1:23:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,do that in a way\Nthat doesn't create more karma
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.77,1:23:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because I would like\Nto continue evolving
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.39,1:23:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,on this path\Nwithout being distracted
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.93,1:23:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by worldly stuff.\NBut having it,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.41,1:23:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,opening up to God's abundance\Nand allowing that to be
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.25,1:23:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and not creating more karma.\NWell, can you accomplish
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.41,1:23:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,some worldly goal\Nwithout creating more karma?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.23,1:23:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.62,1:24:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's,\Nokay,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.65,1:24:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's good enough.\NYou see,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.07,1:24:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you hold in mind\Nthat which you value.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.65,1:24:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what you hold in mind\Nautomatically manifests,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.39,1:24:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,not as a doingness,\Nnot as a this and a that
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.53,1:24:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which creates karma.\NYou hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.05,1:24:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a vision for yourself\Nbecause that which you hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.57,1:24:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to manifest.\NNow it's up to divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.15,1:24:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill it.\NThe divinity of the karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.96,1:24:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.\NMayor?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.47,1:24:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.90,1:24:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What you hold in mind\Ntends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.14,1:24:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated that\Nand that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.38,1:24:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hold it in mind\Nwithout volition,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.14,1:24:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,without trying to make it happen\Nor force it
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.98,1:24:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or cause it or something.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.02,1:24:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMy question is about yoga
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.88,1:24:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and qigong.\NAnd I was seeing
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.10,1:24:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in your new book,\Nwhich of course
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.90,1:24:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't read,\Nbut I was looking
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.18,1:24:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,at somebody else's book.\NAnd hatha yoga
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.22,1:25:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and qigong,\NI forget exactly,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.16,1:25:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but,\Nthey both calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.68,1:25:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,240, 260.\NYeah, positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.48,1:25:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, but I wanted to know
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.24,1:25:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what's wrong with them.\NI didn't say
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.16,1:25:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing wrong with them.\NI see you're over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.12,1:25:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you mean\Nwhat's wrong with them?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.28,1:25:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.\NThe Buddha didn't say
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.98,1:25:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to do that to get enlightened.\NSo I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.56,1:25:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,do you expect it to be 800 or what?\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.80,1:25:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWell, the reason I asked
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.66,1:25:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is that I love,\NI teach those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.98,1:25:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I love teaching them.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.88,1:25:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to make sure\Nthat I wasn't teaching
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.06,1:25:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,something false.\NOh, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.36,1:25:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They're very integrous.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.42,1:25:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, but I mean,\Nif you compare that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.10,1:25:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to like modern medical science,\Nwhich is at 400,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.08,1:25:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought,\Nwell, why shouldn't I just tell
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.82,1:25:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all my yoga students\Njust go to the doctor?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.24,1:25:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't make sense to me.\NYou don't go to a doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.26,1:25:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for spiritual advancement,\Ndo you?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.30,1:25:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it didn't make sense.\NSo you're trying to apply
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.40,1:25:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,apples and peaches.\NThey're two different realms,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.46,1:25:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NNo, what she's doing
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.12,1:26:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is she's saying that\N240 is lower than 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.88,1:26:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NBut you're comparing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.16,1:26:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of apples and pears\Nand they're two different things.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.76,1:26:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so.\NYeah, well, going to the Louvre,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.68,1:26:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, there's pictures\Nin the Louvre that are 700.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.98,1:26:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you shouldn't be doing\Nwhat you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.56,1:26:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be sending\Nall these people to the Louvre.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.34,1:26:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Send everybody to the Louvre\Nand give up whatever you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.32,1:26:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, so, but.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.22,1:26:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that's important\Nis what you're doing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.70,1:26:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is over 200.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.38,1:26:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it?\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.28,1:26:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it matter\Nthat I love what I'm doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.42,1:26:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.\NIt doesn't matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.62,1:26:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIt doesn't matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.50,1:26:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, you're only asking\Nabout a mechanical technique.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.64,1:26:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not asking about\Nthe intention of the practitioner,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.06,1:26:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which is probably\Nfar more powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.54,1:26:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,than the technique.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.26,1:26:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of your intention\Nand your love for your patients,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.14,1:26:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, they're going to do fine.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.92,1:26:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, somebody who calibrates\Nto 180 and is doing these things
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.62,1:26:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,just for the money,\Nyou know, maybe their people
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.28,1:26:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,don't get better, you see.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.14,1:26:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So.\NSo the most important thing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.88,1:27:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is my intention as a practitioner.\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.38,1:27:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.\NAnd then the technique.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.36,1:27:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the technique\Nis just the mechanism,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.82,1:27:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the means, you know.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.52,1:27:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.34,1:27:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's,\Nis there anything wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.34,1:27:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with yoga or qigong?\NI just want to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.36,1:27:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.86,1:27:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NThey're okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.50,1:27:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They're integrous.\NThey're above 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.30,1:27:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They're integrous.\NThey're in line with truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.60,1:27:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, good.\NAnd so, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.22,1:27:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThey're healing techniques.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.00,1:27:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.68,1:27:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, look at it.\NShe's integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.49,1:27:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why she asked.\NShe wants to just verify
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.97,1:27:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the integrity.\NShe did it because
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.59,1:27:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,there's so many bogus things\Nout there, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.65,1:27:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And she just wants to make sure.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.16,1:27:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen many times\Nyou perform kinesiological testing
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.98,1:27:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with Susan.\NAnd I know in power versus force,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.38,1:27:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you describe a technique\Nthat you can perform
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.98,1:28:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on your own.\NCould you go to that again?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.38,1:28:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI can't find it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.40,1:28:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've looked at the book all over.\NShe should demonstrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.16,1:28:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you demonstrate\Nthe self?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.90,1:28:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants to know\Nkinesiology testing
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.26,1:28:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,like the self.\NOh, the ring finger.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.72,1:28:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.30,1:28:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people can do it themselves.\NI say kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.12,1:28:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is like riding a bicycle.\NSome people are gifted
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.14,1:28:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to get it right away.\NOther people struggle
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.70,1:28:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep falling off the bicycle.\NYou hold Abraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.12,1:28:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You hold these two fingers\Nlike this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.26,1:28:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, use this like a hook.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.68,1:28:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm holding Abraham Lincoln\Nin mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.72,1:28:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I,\Nwell, that's saying it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.65,1:28:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying anything\Nabout Abraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.85,1:28:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just holding Abraham Lincoln\Nin my mind, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.78,1:28:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm doing?\NThumb and third finger.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.35,1:28:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNow, I use this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.59,1:28:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I make a hook out of this.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.68,1:28:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNow, I hold these together
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.70,1:28:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,strongly.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.01,1:28:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm holding Abraham Lincoln\Nin mind
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.03,1:28:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and I try to break the ring.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.23,1:28:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Do that.\NNo way.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.70,1:29:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.44,1:29:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.60,1:29:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NStop that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.46,1:29:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNow, hold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.46,1:29:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.\NHold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.10,1:29:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.\NHold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.22,1:29:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.\NHold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.26,1:29:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.\NHold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.34,1:29:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.\NHold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.42,1:29:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.\NHold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.58,1:29:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.\NHold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.64,1:29:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold.\NStop laughing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.54,1:29:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold Ben Loudman in mind.\NPicture Ben Loudman.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.70,1:29:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,His staff and all that.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.62,1:29:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNow, pull your fingers apart again.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.16,1:29:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You see any difference in the strength?\NActually, not the tip of your finger,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.50,1:29:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually higher up, I noticed.\NWhat you're saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.90,1:29:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NWhat are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.50,1:29:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're trying to make something\Nvery simple and complicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.02,1:29:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You just go like this\Nand you go like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.28,1:29:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.98,1:29:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it.\NYou don't have to go to college for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.48,1:29:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do that.\NIt doesn't have to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.02,1:29:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The best thing to do\Nis it isn't a test of strength.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.16,1:29:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.34,1:29:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a test of relative strength.\NWhat it is is you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.28,1:29:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when you feel,\Nyou get the feel of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.78,1:29:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nyou put it in
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.92,1:29:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say,\Nokay, Ben Loudman.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.38,1:29:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.18,1:29:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another way of doing it.\NYou take something
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.10,1:29:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that weighs a couple pounds\Nlike a brick.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.88,1:29:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.30,1:29:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold this up in front of you\Nabout the chest height.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.82,1:29:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a new way\NI'm showing everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.94,1:29:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.84,1:30:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, hold Abraham Lincoln in mind\Nand now lift this.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.60,1:30:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.55,1:30:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,hold Ben Loudman in mind\Nand try and lift it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.24,1:30:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It weighs a great deal more\Nwhen I hold Ben Loudman
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.66,1:30:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have much more difficulty\Nlifting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.49,1:30:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something\NI just came across recently.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.71,1:30:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't really tested it out\Nso I'm not recommending it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.37,1:30:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nyou heard it here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.57,1:30:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was trying to do it.\NHow can I do it all by myself?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.29,1:30:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See,\Nother than this technique
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.51,1:30:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think somebody said it there\Nor something.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.95,1:30:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know,\Nyou lift a certain weight
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.87,1:30:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,holding one thing in mind\Nand then lift the same weight
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.09,1:30:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,holding something else in mind.\NAnd just compare the amount
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.57,1:30:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of strength it takes.\NAnd I found I could do kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.65,1:30:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,on my own\Neven when she's doing something else
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.83,1:30:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,out in the garden.\NPractice makes perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.37,1:30:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a comparison\Nof the relative ease.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.59,1:30:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell.\NIt takes a lot of effort
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.69,1:30:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to lift these bricks\Nwhen I hold him in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.41,1:31:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I hold him in line\Nit seems to go easier.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.43,1:31:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NOkay, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.27,1:31:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think\Nabout pendulum work?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.16,1:31:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nit's useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.76,1:31:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I would not use it\Nin the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.54,1:31:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't check out\Nthe universe
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.48,1:31:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of the lower astral\Nwith a pendulum.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.78,1:31:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're inviting like lightning\Nto hit your rod.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.38,1:31:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NWe were going to do
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.82,1:31:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a healing prayer.\NWe were going to do
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.38,1:31:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a healing prayer.\NThere's a lot of people here
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.04,1:31:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for healings\Nand could we do
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.68,1:31:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a healing prayer?\NI don't know what that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.34,1:31:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.83,1:31:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOut of body again.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.50,1:31:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.83,1:32:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the healing prayer?\NWhat are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.56,1:32:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nit's my joy
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.74,1:32:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to be with you\Nas usual
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.06,1:32:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and we look forward\Nto the next time.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.76,1:32:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say,\Nwe're evolving
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.04,1:32:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,into a very,\Nvery powerful group.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.88,1:32:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Very powerful group.\NGroup intention
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.40,1:32:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of a people this advanced\Nimpacts the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.05,1:32:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It lifts the overall field\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.71,1:32:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind.\NIt benefits everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.09,1:32:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,not on a causal,\Nnot on a causal,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.43,1:32:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of this causing of that.\NAs a consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.27,1:32:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which we have become\Nto align yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.11,1:32:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender yourself\Nto divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.02,1:32:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfill your karmic\Npotentiality to the fullest,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.88,1:32:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what more can you do?\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.79,1:32:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to live\Nin such a way
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.35,1:32:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that your life is a prayer.\NI want you to live
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.91,1:32:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your life in such a way\Nthat you have no
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.55,1:32:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,anxiety at all\Nabout meeting God.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.71,1:32:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you willing\Nto be answerable
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.27,1:32:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for who you are\Nand what you've done
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.71,1:33:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with what you are?\NWhat more can you ask?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.83,1:33:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What more can you ask?\NThat I live in such a way
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.71,1:33:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that frankly,\NI'm not scared
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.29,1:33:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of talking to God.\NI've done the damnedest I can
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.99,1:33:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in every direction here.\NI've pushed myself
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.35,1:33:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to the limit\Nto be the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.59,1:33:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of my potential.\NThat relieves me
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.14,1:33:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of all guilt\Nbecause now I can make
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.84,1:33:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a mistake.\NYes, I make a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.89,1:33:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the overall context,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.33,1:33:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've sanctified\Nthat mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.10,1:33:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,By your overall intention.\NSo, by intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.98,1:33:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,then,\Nour life becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.14,1:33:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the devotion.\NWe become the prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.64,1:33:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of that,\Nwe invoke divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.94,1:33:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then through the heart,\Nthrough the heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.14,1:33:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,through the devotion,\Nthrough the alignment
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.73,1:33:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with divinity,\Nwe empower all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.84,1:33:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.32,1:34:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we say,\NGloria in excelsis,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.24,1:34:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Deo.\NGlory
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.29,1:34:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to God\Nin the highest.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.00,1:34:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And what more\Ncould be said?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.41,1:34:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nhow far in the room?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.17,1:34:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't know.\NNow, if you like it,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.71,1:34:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll spend more and more time\Nwith individual questions
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.03,1:34:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and answers\Nand I'll leave it up
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.39,1:34:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the group.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.36,1:34:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave it up to the group.\NLet's do it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.99,1:34:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Would people favor\Nmore time
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.79,1:34:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with personal questions\Nand answers
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.49,1:34:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and spontaneous interviews?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.79,1:34:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Vis-a-vis didactic teaching.\NLet's see the answer for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.83,1:35:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've got a lot of scholars here, too.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.47,1:35:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, well, you know,\Nwe make it half and half
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.33,1:35:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're always discovering new things\Nand therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.53,1:35:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to present it on every level\Nfrom the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.79,1:35:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the intellect,\Nfrom the mind, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.53,1:35:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we,\Nthe reason doesn't,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.69,1:35:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't just stuck in 400\Nbecause you see reason
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.01,1:35:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of itself\Ncalibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.41,1:35:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you use reason\Nas a means
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.27,1:35:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of\Npursuing,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.35,1:35:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,pursuing God,\Npursuing spiritual intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.37,1:35:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,then you've sanctified the intellect.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.81,1:35:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not just using it\Nfor its own egoistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.93,1:35:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nyou can sanctify
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.71,1:35:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,your intellect\Nand you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.37,1:35:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for the old Lord,\NLord,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.09,1:35:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,do I try to understand\Nand incorporate these teachings
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.53,1:35:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that they may bring me closer\Nto the old Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.07,1:35:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can sanctify\Nthe mind
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.05,1:35:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,essentially.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.47,1:35:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is different than a secular mind\Nwhich is only looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.37,1:36:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to squeeze\Nthe gain out of information.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.65,1:36:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.99,1:36:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,let's,\Nhow's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.01,1:36:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll sanctify the mind collectively.\NOh Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.58,1:36:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we do surrender our collective minds\Nto thy service
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.96,1:36:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that we may\Nbe
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.26,1:36:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the fulfillment\Nof thy potential
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.88,1:36:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in this demand,\Nin this dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.38,1:36:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.\NIt's okay to be an intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.84,1:36:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NOh, golly.
